# Frontend Patterns

## Theme Integration ‚Äî NEVER hardcode colors

```tsx
// ‚úÖ CORRECT ‚Äî semantic Tailwind classes
<div className="bg-background text-primary border-weak">
<span className="text-error">Error occurred</span>

// ‚ùå WRONG ‚Äî hardcoded colors break dark/light mode
<div className="bg-gray-900 text-white border-gray-700">
```

**Semantic classes:**
- Backgrounds: `bg-background` `bg-secondary` `bg-surface` `bg-canvas` `bg-elevated`
- Text: `text-primary` `text-secondary` `text-disabled` `text-link`
- Borders: `border-weak` `border-medium` `border-strong`
- Status: `text-success` `text-warning` `text-error` `text-info`

Prefer `@grafana/ui` components over custom implementations.

## Error Handling ‚Äî No silent failures, no console.*

```tsx
// ‚úÖ CORRECT ‚Äî surface errors in the UI
} catch (err) {
  setError('Failed to load tools. Please try again.');
}

// ‚ùå WRONG ‚Äî swallowed error, console pollution
} catch (err) {
  console.error(err);
}
```

No `console.log`, `console.error`, or `console.warn` in shipped code.

## Component Patterns

- Functional components with hooks only ‚Äî no class components
- `async/await` not `.then()/.catch()`
- Custom hooks for reusable business logic (`useChat`, `useSessionManager`)
- `useMemo` / `useCallback` for performance-sensitive computations

## Testing Selectors

Always use `data-testid` attributes from `src/components/testIds.ts`:

```tsx
// ‚úÖ
<button data-testid={testIds.chat.sendButton}>Send</button>

// ‚ùå
<button id="send-btn" className="send-button">Send</button>
```

## Session & Org Isolation

- All UserStorage keys must include orgId: `grafana-o11y-chat-org-{orgId}-*`
- Sessions are private per user ‚Äî never share across users
- Max 50 sessions per user per org (auto-eviction of oldest)
